#
# PGSD -- Kernel configuration for the PGSD distribution
#
# This is a derivative of FreeBSD GENERIC at the time of PGSD's
# creation; see /usr/src/sys/amd64/conf/GENERIC for upstream and
# config(5) for the file format. Re-merge with upstream GENERIC
# when tracking new FreeBSD releases.
#
# PGSD owns the input layer through inputfs (per AD-1 in the
# project BACKLOG.md and the inputfs ADR series at
# inputfs/docs/adr/). To give inputfs uncontested ownership of HID
# devices, drivers that would otherwise claim USB HID children at
# boot are removed from the kernel image AND from the modules
# build. Removing the device line from this config keeps the
# driver out of the static kernel image; that is the kernel-side
# half. The other half is suppressing the .ko files at modules
# build time, which is done by passing WITHOUT_MODULES on the
# command line to make buildkernel and make installkernel.
# pgsd-kernel/README.md documents the procedure.
#
# A makeoptions WITHOUT_MODULES=... directive in this config
# would NOT reliably suppress the modules. The kernel-config
# makeoptions reach the kernel-link step but the modules tree is
# invoked from /usr/src/Makefile.inc1 via a separate make that
# does not always inherit them. The supported and reliable path
# is the command-line argument; the README is the single source
# of truth for that procedure.
#
# Removed devices (compete with inputfs for HID ownership):
#   - hkbd    HID keyboard driver, claims hidbus children
#   - ukbd    USB keyboard driver, claims USB devices before
#             hidbus sees them
#
# Devices retained that inputfs depends on:
#   - hid     generic HID layer, parser, descriptor handling
#   - hidbus  HID bus driver; inputfs attaches here per ADR 0007
#   - usbhid  USB-to-HID transport, required by hidbus over USB
#
# Anticipatory module suppressions (drivers named in ADR 0007 that
# may appear in a future GENERIC or be loaded on demand even when
# absent from the static kernel; the README's WITHOUT_MODULES list
# excludes them at build time):
#   hms hgame hcons hsctrl hpen hmt hconf
#     HID class drivers superseded by inputfs
#   hidmap
#     HID-to-evdev mapping framework; PGSD/UTF excludes evdev as
#     a structural commitment, see ADR 0001
#
# Out of scope for this config (deliberate):
#   evdev, uinput, EVDEV_SUPPORT remain enabled. Removing the
#   evdev userland contract is a separate architectural decision
#   with broader consequences for userland compatibility during
#   the PGSD transition period; tracked separately, not folded
#   into AD-8.
#
# For more on the FreeBSD kernel config grammar see config(5)
# and /usr/src/sys/conf/NOTES.
#

