# Sound support
#
# AD-3: the snd(4) framework is removed from PGSD in full.
# PGSD's audiofs(4) substrate owns the PCI HDA controller
# class (class MULTIMEDIA, subclass MULTIMEDIA_HDA per the
# PCI spec) via direct PCI attachment per ADR 0006; the
# match is vendor-agnostic and covers both analog and HDMI
# HDA controllers. The other in-tree snd drivers (cmi, csa,
# emu10kx, es137x, ich, via8233) target legacy / non-HDA
# hardware that PGSD does not aim to support; they are
# removed rather than left in-tree as latent dead code.
# The generic `sound` shim is removed for the same reason
# - with no driver registering into it, it provides nothing
# at runtime, and keeping it would suggest an /dev/dsp*
# fallback path that the AD-3 endpoint forecloses.
#
# Originally, snd_hda specifically was removed because it
# would create hdacc children with a name-locked driver
# binding, preventing audiofs from attaching at the codec
# slot. With Option A (full snd(4) retirement) applied, the
# wider rationale is "if PGSD does not target the hardware,
# the kernel does not compile in the driver", consistent
# with AD-8 (HID exclusions) and AD-39 (console drivers).
#
# As with the AD-8 HID exclusions, the .ko files are
# suppressed at build time via the WITHOUT_MODULES list in
# pgsd-kernel-build.sh; these device lines are absent from
# the static kernel.

